=== TASK ===
# Booking Create / Edit Wizard

## Overview
Develop a full-featured Booking Create / Edit Wizard within LuxeFlow CRM that guides users step-by-step through creating or editing a luxury travel booking. The wizard must support selecting or creating a client, selecting resort and room, choosing rate plans and calculating commissions, configuring a payment schedule, adding itinerary items, attaching supplier references, and saving as a quote or confirming the booking. It must include automated checks for conflicts and deadlines, integrate with the Booking Lifecycle & Management system (timeline, attachments, internal handoffs, supplier references), and support generation of Proposal & Handover templates (DOCX/PDF) populated from booking data. The Booking Detail page must present a full record including timeline, itinerary, resort & room details, rate details, commission structure, payment schedule, deadlines, supplier references, attachments, internal notes, and approval workflows. This project sits inside the LuxeFlow CRM for luxury travel operations and must meet strict UI/UX, data integrity, and security requirements, with strong permissions and scalability.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The Booking Create / Edit Wizard page drives step-by-step booking creation and editing, including client selection/creation, resort & room selection, rate plans, commission models, and a configurable payment schedule. It also supports adding itinerary items, transferring data to attachments and supplier references, and saving bookings as quotes or confirmed bookings. It integrates with automated checks for conflicts (date and resource clashes), deadlines, and the overall Booking Lifecycle.

Goals:
- Enable agents to rapidly create or edit bookings with guided validation at each step.
- Auto-populate client information when an existing client is selected; allow seamless creation of a new client with validation and defaults.
- Allow Resort Bible search and filtering to find suitable resorts/rooms with rich attributes (transfer times, kids policy, seasonality, etc.).
- Let users select rate plans, contract terms, and auto-calculate commissions based on a configurable model.
- Define a flexible payment schedule with milestones, due dates, amounts, and currency handling; enforce deadlines and SLA constraints.
- Create and attach itinerary items (day-level editor, transfers, activities), with time blocks and dependencies.
- Attach supplier references and documents; manage internal notes and handoffs.
- Offer “Save as Quote” or “Confirm Booking” actions with validation, including conflict checks and deadline compliance.
- Provide a live Progress Bar and Save Draft capability; show real-time validation feedback.
- Generate standardized Proposal & Handover outputs (DOCX/PDF) populated from the booking data on demand.
- Navigate to Booking Detail after save/edit, showing full lifecycle timeline (quote → confirmed → pre-arrival → in-stay → post-stay), itinerary, room/resort details, rates, commission structure, payment schedules, deadlines, supplier references, attachments, internal notes, and approval flows.

UI elements and how they should look:
- Step-based wizard with a prominent progress bar, clearly labeled steps, and the ability to save drafts and move back/forward with validation at each step.
- Step 1: Client Selection/Creation
  - Auto-populate fields (passport, contact preferences, billing details, VIP flags) when an existing client is chosen.
  - Form to search existing clients, select, or create a new client with validation.
- Step 2: Resort & Room Selection
  - Resort Bible search embedded with filters (kids policy, transfer time, location, beach proximity, room types, capacity).
  - Card-based resort results with image, summary, and a selectable room category; show transfer time and inclusions.
- Step 3: Rates & Commission
  - Display rate plans with pricing, inclusions, terms, and cancellation windows.
  - Commission model selection with auto-calculation (tiered, flat, percentage) and summary.
- Step 4: Payment Schedule & Deadlines
  - Create an editable milestone-based payment schedule (deposit, interim payments, balance).
  - View and adjust due dates, amounts, currency, payment methods; flag overdue or upcoming deadlines.
- Step 5: Itinerary & Transfers
  - Day-level itinerary editor with add/edit/remove days, activities, transfers, and times.
  - Visual timeline for clarity; drag-and-drop reordering where appropriate.
- Step 6: Attachments & Supplier References
  - Attach documents (contracts, supplier quotes); capture supplier references and contact details.
- Step 7: Review & Save (quote or confirm)
  - Summary view with all sections collapsed/expanded; validation panel showing issues and how to fix.
  - Actions: Save Draft, Save as Quote, Confirm Booking; button states reflect validation status.
- Progress Bar and Save Draft
  - Persistent progress indicator; allow saving draft at any stage; retain unsaved changes with autosave hints.
- Visual guidance
  - Subtle tooltips, inline validation messages, and contextual help to guide users through complex fields.
- Connected components
  - Booking Lifecycle timeline widget on the detail view.
  - Inline conflict/deadline indicators wherever relevant (e.g., overlapping itineraries, supplier deadlines).

UI/UX guidelines used:
- Architecture emphasizes a luxurious, calm, and efficient experience with generous whitespace, clear typography, and consistent micro-interactions.
- Emphasis on readability, accessible color contrast, responsive behavior, and keyboard-friendly navigation.
- Data-heavy inputs are segmented into cards with light dividers, soft shadows, and rounded corners per the design system.

