  - Booking state persisted in backend; live synchronization for timeline and status
  - Templates generate using booking payload; placeholders replaced with actual data

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] The wizard supports create and edit flows with all seven steps, including client creation and auto-population.
- [ ] All arrays are initialized with [] and guarded with Array.isArray() before map/filter/reduce usage.
- [ ] Null/undefined values are never passed to array methods; results from API are normalized using data ?? [] or Array.isArray checks.
- [ ] Validation runs at each step; Save Draft is always possible; Save as Quote and Confirm Booking are disabled until validation passes.
- [ ] Conflict and deadline checks run in real-time (or on save) and surface actionable error messages.
- [ ] Booking Detail shows full lifecycle timeline and all fields (itinerary, resort, room, rate, commission, payments, deadlines, references, attachments, internal notes, approvals).
- [ ] Proposal & Handover templates generate correctly from booking data and produce valid DOCX/PDF outputs with proper placeholders replaced.
- [ ] Role-based access controls prevent unauthorized actions; Admin/Agent/Ops/Finance permissions enforced.
- [ ] Accessible keyboard navigation, responsive UI, and performance considerations (debounced search, lazy rendering, etc.)

## UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project’s design system:

- Color Palette:
  - Primary: White (#FFFFFF)
  - Accent: Olive Green (#8A9A5B)
  - Neutrals: #F6F6F6, #EEEEEE
  - Text: #222222; secondary #888888
